# UiPath Project Rule

The full rule lives in CLAUDE.md at the repo root. Read it before acting.

Before any action in a UiPath repo:
1. Read CLAUDE.md (principles, hard gates, decision logic).
2. Check that the `skills/` submodule guard passed for this session
   (run `python -m uipath_claude.skills.submodule_guard` if unsure).
3. Identify the project type (CLAUDE.md §1).
4. For CLI syntax, read docs/uipath-cli.md.
5. For end-to-end flows, read docs/uipath-workflows.md.

Hard gates:
- The `skills/` submodule is the source of truth for UiPath skills.
  Do not hand-roll a skill that already lives there; extend via `extensions/skills/`.
- Modern experience only: C#, Windows, .NET 8. No Classic, no VB.Net.
- Never publish if `analyze` returns errors.
- Never commit .env or secrets.
- CLI version must match Studio version.
- Solutions are Automation Cloud only.
- Never deploy to Production from an AI-assistant session.

Three CLIs:
- `uipcli` (.NET) for RPA / Coded Automations / Solutions / CI.
- `uipath` (Python) for coded agents (LangGraph, LlamaIndex, generic).
- `uip` (Node.js) for skill-level ops (discovery, Case, Data Fabric, Coded Apps, Servo, feedback).

Build loop: restore -> analyze (gate) -> test (gate) -> pack -> deploy (personal workspace) -> smoke test.

Start every build task by running the uipath-project-discovery-agent
(`skills/agents/uipath-project-discovery-agent.md`) to populate
`.claude/rules/project-context.md`. Project-specific conventions live there,
not in CLAUDE.md.

See CLAUDE.md for the complete rule.
